  <h2>Why you should use four different digits for keypad locks</h2>
  <p class="auth">Posted by Jonas Elfström
  <span class="typo_date" title="Wed, 23 Sep 2009 17:49:00 GMT">Wed, 23 Sep 2009 17:49:00 GMT</span></p>
  <p>I made a couple of very bad mistakes in this article so I took it down. Hopefully I'm more on track in the <a href="../27/a-case-for-using-only-three-different-digits-in-keypad-codes">sequel</a>.</p>
</div>
<p class="meta">
  Posted in <a href="http://alicebobandmallory.com/articles/category/security" rel="noindex, follow, tag">Security</a>, <a href="http://alicebobandmallory.com/articles/category/ruby" rel="noindex, follow, tag">Ruby</a>&nbsp;<strong>|</strong>&nbsp;<a href="why-you-should-use-four-different-digits-for-keypad-locks#comments">3 comments</a>
</p>

